description.plain:
“Twerkulator” is a song by City Girls that was supposed to be on their album City On Lock, but it didn’t make the final track list. The song leaked along with the rest of the album on the day before release, but “Twerkulator” was the only song from the leak that did not make the final track list.

In March 2021, JT’s verse started to go viral on social media app Tik Tok. On March 23rd, Yung Miami explained via Twitter that the sample the song was based around was unable to get cleared, hence its exclusion from the album. https://twitter.com/YungMiami305/status/1374553162976260096

However, on May 18, 2021, the City Girls announced that “Twerkulator” would finally receive an official release that Friday, May 21, likely for a deluxe version of City On Lock if it isn’t a standalone single.
https://twitter.com/citygirls/status/1394733589003046912

After being in prison for over a year on charges of credit card fraud, Jatavia Johnson, better known as JT of the City Girls, reentered the music scene with a track that makes sure to set the opposition straight.
